# __Item Catalog Project__

`WEI-CHEN LIN` 

#### Discription of project

This project will list items within a variety of categoies. User can create the category and add the items they want. 

#### Skills used for this project

- Python 
- HTML
- Flask
- SQLAchemy

#### Things needed to run this application

- [Vagrant](https://www.vagrantup.com/)
- [Udacity Vagrantfile](https://github.com/udacity/fullstack-nanodegree-vm)
- [VirtualBox](https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads)


#### How to Run the files? 

- Install Vagrant and VirtualBox
- Clone the Vagrantfile from the Udacity Repo
- Copy this file into the 'catalog' folder
- Using git Bash, go into the 'catalog' folder
- Run `vagrant up` to run the virtual machine
- Then `vagrant ssh` to login to the VM
- Run application with `python application.py`
- Then, go to `http://localhost/categories` to see the website

#### Project Flaws

- Cannot do the user registration and authentication system
- Google discontinue doing Google+ Sign in from March 7, 2019 [Link] (https://developers.google.com/identity/sign-in/web/quick-migration-guide)
- As a result, the codes from lessons are not working at all. 
